        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 1:39PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 139 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Curtis Station, or 7 miles west of Batesville, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Curtis Station, Sardis, Mims, Batesville, Riverview, Asa, Hinchcliff,
Glenville, Locke Station, Hayes Crossing, John W Kyle State Park,
Chapeltown, and Courtland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for northwestern
Mississippi.</instruction>
